body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, my name is Noah Miller and I'm a customer service agent at AutoTech Solutions. What's your name please?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Diane. Can you please provide me with your email address for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And could you also confirm your phone number for us, if you don't mind?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my phone number is five five five - three three three - two two two two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Diane. Is there anything specific you'd like to discuss today regarding your billing inquiries at the dealership?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling nervous about some unexpected charges on my recent invoice.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Diane. Let's go over the charges together to clarify everything. I appreciate your patience.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time today, Diane. I'll look into the issue further and get back to you with a resolution. Have a great day.
